Visits to DPRK embassies 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 13 (KCNA) -- A delegation of the Khmer Combatants Party for Mulinaka and Liberty of Cambodia led by the acting chairman paid a visit to the DPRK embassy in Phnom Penh on April 7 to commemorate Sun's Day, the birth anniversary of the President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In Guyana leader of the Amerindian Action Movement Peter Persaud, chairman of the Guyana Committee for Support to Korea's Reunification Sabid Bacus and general secretary of the Good Green Guyana Robert Williams visited the DPRK embassy in Georgetown between April 4 and 6 to commemorate Sun's Day and the 7th anniversary of the great leader Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The visitors laid baskets of flowers before the portraits of Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il at the embassies.

National symposium held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 13 (KCNA) -- A national symposium was held here on Wednesday to commemorate the 88th birth anniversary of the President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Present there were Choe Thae Bok, Yang Hyong Sop, Kim Ki Nam and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The symposium explained in a deep-going way the great revolutionary exploits of the President, who devoted himself to the freedom and happiness of people and opened a rosy future with the Juche era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Thae Hyong Chol, president of the Academy of Social Sciences, referring to the great changes with the advent of the Juche era, said that it is a great event in human history which brought about an essential turn in carving out the destiny of the popular masses and in socio-political life that Kim Il Sung ushered in the Juche era, a new era of human history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Kim Ki Bin, vice-president of Kim Il Sung Higher Party School, stressed that the wise leadership of Kim Il Sung developed the Worker's Party of Korea into the most authoritative party recognized by the world and successfully solved the inheritance of the party's leadership to make the party promising. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Kang Tok So, deputy editor of Rodong Sinmun, said the President achieved the single-hearted unity of the party and the revolutionary ranks and built up the driving force of the revolution, which is one of his most brilliant revolutionary exploits for which he lives forever as a peerlessly great master of politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Kim Ryong Song, first deputy department director of the secretariat of the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland, deeply explained that the President laid firm foundations for national reunification and opened a bright prospect for reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Cha Kyong Il, vice-president of Kim Il Sung University of Politics, said the President's life is shining as the life of an outstanding leader of the world revolution and the international communist movement, who performed immortal revolutionary exploits in the cause of global independence and the history of the human liberation struggle in the most noble spirit of internationalism and on the anti-imperialist and revolutionary principle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Kim Chun Gun, department head of Kim Il Sung University, said there is no more honorable and sacred work for the WPK and the Korean people than to make the new century shine as Kim Jong Il's century. Herein lie the eternal life of the President, the final victory of the Juche revolutionary cause started in the forests of Mt. Paektu and the eternal prosperity of the Korean people and humankind, he added.

Pakistani charge d'affaires ad interim hosts reception 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, April 13 (KCNA) -- M. Ayaz Khan, charge d'affaires ad interim of the Islamic Republic of Pakistan to the DPRK, hosted a reception at Pyongyang Koryo Hotel yesterday on the occasion of Sun's Day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He in his speech at the reception said that April 15, the birth anniversary of the President Kim Il Sung, is a significant day in the history of the DPRK and he deemed it a great honor and privilege to join the Korean people in commemorating   Sun's Day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He said that the august name of the President is a symbol of freedom, peace and progress, adding that the President energetically worked all his life for the sake of the oppressed people and always stood by the progressive people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Pointing out that the whole world, developing countries in particular, are greatly inspired by his farsighted idea and the Pakistani people learn a lot from the successes achieved in the DPRK under the wise leadership of Marshal Kim Jong Il, he stressed that the revolutionary cause of Juche pioneered by President Kim Il Sung has been successfully carried forward by Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The friendly relations between the two countries are growing stronger as days go by because they were provided by the President, he said, stressing that the President was a great friend of the Pakistani people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Pakistan supports the Korean people in their efforts to achieve national reunification free from interference of foreign forces, he noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Pak Kil yon, vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs, also addressed the reception.

Foreign guests visit Kimilsungia Show 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 13 (KCNA) -- Foreign diplomatic envoys and representatives of international organizations here visited the 2nd Kimilsungia Show yesterday on the occasion of Sun's Day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The guests looked round the show with deep emotion while hearing an explanation about immortal Kimilsungia which came into full bloom thanks to the ardent veneration of all people for the respected leader President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
   At the end of their visit they made entries into the visitor's book. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Noting that Kimilsungia is in full bloom in many countries of the world, Mongolian ambassador Damdiny Byamba wrote that Kim Il Sung will always live in the hearts of the Korean people and other peoples of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Ambassador of the Federal Republic of Nigeria Alhaji Daudu Sulaiman wrote that the immortal flower named after Kim Il Sung is evidence that he enjoyed a high authority not only among the Korean people but among the world people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
Yugoslav charge d'affaires ad interim Milorad Kosovac said he was deeply impressed to watch beautiful Kimilsungia in full bloom, adding: This is something fascinating that can be seen only in the DPRK blessed with the great men.

Cuban charge d'affaires ad interim gives reception 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 13 (KCNA) -- Nirsia Castro Guevara, Cuban charge d'affaires ad interim to the DPRK, gave a reception yesterday on the occasion of Sun's Day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   She in her speech said that the Cuban people cherish the noblest and beautiful memories of the Korean people's great leader Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Recalling that Kim Il Sung visited the Cuban embassy, she noted that the Cuban people look back upon his exploits with deep emotion whenever they commemorate Sun's Day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Noting that the cause of Kim Il Sung has been steadfastly carried forward by the great leader Kim Jong Il, she expressed belief that the Korean people would surely build a powerful socialist nation under the leadership of Kim Jong Il despite all sorts of difficulties. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   She expressed deep thanks to the Korean people for having supported the Cuban people in their struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   She was convinced that the friendly relations between the two countries would continue to develop. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Kim Yong Dae, vice-president of the presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, in his speech at the reception recalled that President Kim Il Sung firmly defended the Cuban revolution and fully supported and encouraged the just cause of the Cuban people materially and morally out of the noble sense of internationalist obligation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He noted that the traditional friendship between the two countries based on the close and intimate relations between President Kim Il Sung and respected Fidel Castro Ruz is being steadily strengthened and developed under the special care of the great leader Kim Jong Il and respected Fidel Castro Ruz. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He sincerely wished the fraternal Cuban people led by Fidel Castro Ruz greater success in the struggle to smash the U.S.'s blockade and moves to stifle Cuba and thus defend the motherland, revolution and gains of socialism.

Pyongyang art festival successfully goes on 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 13 (KCNA) -- The 18th April Spring Friendship Art Festival is successfully going on in different theatres here amid the deepening friendship and solidarity between foreign artistes and the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The performers made a great epical representation of humankind's boundless reverence for the President Kim Il Sung and its faith and will to hold him in high esteem for all ages and highly praised General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Naval Song and Dance Ensemble of the Russian Ministry of Defence put on the stage the immortal revolutionary song "Song of General Kim Jong Il" by wind instrumental music and vocal trio. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Nepalese Art Troupe sang in Korean the song "We Make a Salute To His Excellency Kim Jong Il" which was specially created for this festival. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Malaysian Art Troupe presented female trio of the song "Kimjongilia" which was written and composed by the head of the troupe. In the song it truthfully depicted the immortal beautiful flower now in full bloom in different parts of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Female soloists of Uzbekistan and Cuba and a Cambodian musician sang Korean songs "Leader on Mansu Hill," "Green Pine Standing on Nam Hill," "Song of Three Prides" and so on, winning a warm applause from the audience for their high artistry. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Chinese female dancers presented well Korean dance "dance of jingle," deeply impressing the audience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The festival stages were also decorated with such colourful art pieces as piano solo by international concours  winner Cristiano Grifone of the Italian Art Troupe, Moldovan female vocal solo, cello quartet of German Cellists' Troupe, Polish male vocal solo, song and dance of the Art Troupe of Tajikistan, mixed dance of the Art Troupe of the New Cultural Committee of Indonesia and mixed vocal trio of the French Art Troupe. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
An Austrian musician successfully conducted an orchestra of the overture of the opera "Ruslan and Lyudmila."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The festival continues.

KPA servicemen hold solemn ceremony 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, April 13 (KCNA) -- Soldiers of the three services of the Korean People's Army held a solemn ceremony at the plaza of the Kumsusan Memorial Palace today to pay their respects to the President Kim Il Sung and vow loyalty to the President and General Secretary Kim Jong Il on the occasion of Sun's Day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Present at the ceremony were Jo Myong Rok, director of the general political department of the KPA, Kim Yong Chun, chief of the KPA general staff, Kim Il Chol, Minister of the People's Armed Forces, KPA vice-marshals and commanders of arms and services. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The participants made a salute to the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A 24-gun salute boomed amid the playing of the immortal revolutionary paean "Song of General Kim Il Sung."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Jo Myong Rok in his speech said the Generalissimo devoted his whole life to the sacred cause of the revolution and the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The KPA servicemen will hold the Generalissimo in high esteem as the eternal leader and glorify his noble revolutionary life and immortal exploits for all ages, he said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He stressed the need to strengthen the single-hearted unity of the entire army around Kim Jong Il and further increase their combat readiness. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He emphasized that if the enemies intrude into our land, sea and sky even an inch, the KPA servicemen will deal a merciless, annihilating blow to them to firmly defend the security of the country and the people and surely achieve national reunification.

Message of sympathy to Mongolian President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 13 (KCNA) -- President Kim Yong Nam of the presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK on April 10 sent a message of sympathy to President Nachagyn Bagabandy of Mongolia as regards the recent damage caused by biting cold and heavy snow in areas of Mongolia as a whole. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The message expresses deep sympathy to the President and, through him, to the people  in the afflicted areas as well as conviction that the Mongolian government and people will do away with the consequences of natural disasters  and bring the living of the people in the afflicted areas to normal at an early date.

Foreign diplomatic envoys visit photo exhibition 
  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 13 (KCNA) -- Foreign diplomatic envoys here visited a photo exhibition yesterday on the occasion of the 35th anniversary of the historic visit of General Secretary Kim Jong Il to Indonesia in attendance on the President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Exhibited there are photos showing historic external activities conducted by Kim Il Sung energetically during his state visit to Indonesia, receiving warm welcome from the Indonesian government and people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   On show there are also photos showing unremitting  revolutionary activities of Kim Jong Il who paid a historic visit to Indonesia accompanying the President.

International support to three-point charter of Korea's reunification 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, April 13 (KCNA) -- Youth and student organizations, organizations and personages of all social standings in different countries and regions participated in the signature campaign supporting the three-point charter of Korea's reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Youth and student organizations in different countries and regions took part in the campaign when they attended the 17th meeting of the International Union of Students from March 13 to 19. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The signature paper was signed by the President of the Arab Youth Union on behalf of 7,000,000 members, the international secretary of the Southern Africa Students' Union on behalf of 1,500,000, the general secretary of the India University Students Federation on behalf of 2,500,000, the chairman of the National Union of Students of Chad on behalf of 50,000 and the international secretary of the National Union of Kuwait students on behalf of 30,000. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Participating in the campaign were also ten odd organizations, including the Latin American Continental Organization of Students, the All-Africa Students' Union, the Asian Students Association, the National Union of Ghana Students, the General Association of Students of Rwanda, the National Federation of Students of Benin, the Uganda National Association of Students, the Association of Students of Yaunde University of Cameroon, the National Federation of Students of Costa Rica, the National Union of Students of Philippines, the National Union of Students of Iraq and the General Association of University Students of El Salvador. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
From March 28 to April 5 the signature paper was signed by the governor of the fourth province of Guyana on behalf of 30,000 citizens and the chairman of the Guyanese Union of Agricultural Allied Workers, the chairman of the Corriverton branch of the Guyana Committee for Support to Korea's Reunification, the chairman of the Guyana Torchlight Teakwood Group for the Study of the Juche Idea of comrade Kim Il Sung, the captain of the Kim Il Sung cricket team of Corriverton, Guyana, and the chairman of the Laingavenue, Guyana, group for the study of works of comrade Kim Jong Il on behalf of their organizations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The secretary general of the Peruvian Committee for Supporting the Independent and Peaceful Reunification of Korea, the chairman of the Peruvian Group for the Study of the Literary and Art Ideas of Comrade Kim Jong Il and other public figures of Peru signed the paper in the name of their organizations.

2nd day acrobatic performances 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 13 (KCNA) -- 2nd day performances were given at the Pyongyang Circus Theatre by acrobats from different countries participating in the 18th April Spring Friendship Art Festival, drawing capacity spectators. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The Russian circus, in its acrobatic drama "Prometheus," made a peculiar depiction of the legend about a god who brought fire to human beings, through delicate and skilful movements. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Chinese acrobats presented "women's stunt of jumping from a board" in which they skillfully performed difficult technical movements including somersault, sideways turn and jumping from a board to erect two human towers simultaneously. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   "Hand feats" by a Cuban acrobat, "stunts on an iron rope" by Swedish acrobats, "brick feats" by a Cambodian acrobat and "roller plastic acrobatics" by Vietnamese acrobats drew the acclaim of the spectators. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Sister acrobats of the Mongolian circus put "two women plastic acrobatics" on the stage, in which they demonstrated elegant and skilful techniques and displayed two Kimjongilias at the end of their performance, making deep reverence for General Secretary Kim Jong Il prevail in the theatre.

2nd Kimilsungia Show 
  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 13 (KCNA) -- The 2nd Kimilsungia Show was open at the Pyongyang International House of Culture in Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Exhibited are thousands of potted flowers Kimilsungia  presented by many units and individuals in all parts of the country, including the ministries of the people's armed forces and people's security, the Academy of Sciences, the Central Botanical Garden of the bureau for the management of Mt. Taesong and South Phyongan Province. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   All show cases are conspicuously decorated by large pictures and posters and the soft tune of "Song of General Kim Il Sung" and "Nostalgia" stirs the emotion of visitors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The background of the show case presented by the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces depicts the native home in Mangyongdae, the cradle of revolution, and the Kumsusan Memorial Palace against a red flag, which intensively show the glorious revolutionary history of the President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Placed in the center is a statue (picture) of the President in the uniform of Generalissimo over at least 400 Kimilsungia flowers and 88 Kimjongilia flowers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   On the right side of the background are golden letters "the great leader comrade Kim Il Sung will always be with us" and "immortality" written on a marble tower and a flower stand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Ministry of People's Security decorates the show case with a portrait of the President with sunny smile in his face against the background of the Kumsusan memorial palace in its center,  letters "immortality" and "Sun's Day" in both sides and over 400 Kimilsungia flowers, more than 20 Kimjongilia flowers  and other flowers on seven flights of stairs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Academy of Sciences has put on display hundreds of Kimilsungia flowers on several flights of steps with a portrait of the President with sunny smile in his face against the background of Kimilsungia in full bloom in a large picture board illuminated by electric beam. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Also displayed are Kimilsungia flowers from tissue cultivation to bloom, which are computerized. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Kimilsungia from the Indonesian embassy here is on display. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
And put on show are over 80 potted flowers including gift flowers rhododendron Indicum (8 species), Hippeastrum Hydridum and tropical plants from five continents.

Talks held between delegations of WPK and PPC 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 13 (KCNA) -- Talks were held in Pyongyang today between the delegations of the Worker's Party of Korea and the People's Party of Cambodia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   At the talks both sides exchanged views on the issue of developing the friendly and cooperative relations between the two parties and a series of issues of mutual concern. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Present at the talks were Kim Yang Gon, department director of the WPK Central Committee, and officials concerned and members of the PPC delegation led by vice-chairman of the control committee of the PPC Ney Pena, who is also member of the standing commission of the central committee of its party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The talks proceeded in a friendly atmosphere.

Korean people and army will retaliate against provocation by enemy 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 13 (KCNA) -- The spokesman for the Foreign Ministry of the DPRK denounced the United States for planning to start a week-long maneuver for a war of aggression called "reception, staging, onward-movement and integration exercise" together with the South Korean authorities on April 15 and demanded an immediate halt to the maneuver. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In a statement issued today he said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   An agreement has been reached on historic inter-Korean summit talks, the first of its kind since the liberation of Korea from the Japanese colonial rule, a series of dialogue and negotiations for the establishment of diplomatic ties are now under way among the DPRK and parties concerned which have been hostile toward the former and a friendship festival of artistes from many countries around the world who are aspiring after independence and peace is successfully going on in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
    How can the powder-reeking war exercise the U.S. is going to stage at this time be interpreted: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The U.S. is describing the projected maneuver as an annual event in a bid to water down the offensive nature of the maneuver. But the realities prove that "detente" and "improved relations" on the lips of the U.S. are nothing but hypocrisy to cover up the true colors as a war-thirsty country and aggressor and mislead public opinion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   If the U.S. truly wants peace and stability on the Korean peninsula and has the willingness to discharge its obligation under the DPRK-U.S. agreed framework that bans threatening the other side by force of arms and implement it with sincerity, it should immediately discontinue all the war exercises getting on the nerves of the DPRK and threatening it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Dialogue and war are incompatible. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Korean people and army keep a close watch, with heightened vigilance, on the U.S. reckless moves for escalating tensions going on behind the curtain of "dialogue" and "detente." They will take a strong countermeasure against possible provocations by the enemies.

Hanchongryon chairman elected 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   Pyongyang, April 13 (KCNA) -- The South Korean Federation of University Student Councils (Hanchongryon) reportedly held a meeting of its 8th-term deputies on April 8, at which Ri Hui Chol, chairman of the General Student Council of Chosun University, was elected chairman of Hanchongryon.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   His election was decided through the balloting of over 900 deputies from regional federations that day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Meanwhile, Hanchongryon declared that it would hold a meeting to decide on the orientation of students movement, rallies of regional federations and a ceremony to inaugurate its special committee for probe into the truth behind the GIs' massacres.

Students urged to rise in anti-U.S., anti-dictatorship struggle 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 13 (KCNA) -- The youth and student department of the central committee of the National Democratic Front of South Korea released an "appeal to one million students" on April 8, the Seoul-based radio Voice of National Salvation reported. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The appeal said that the South Korean authorities are resorting to divide-and-crush tactics to repress students in the valiant spring struggle. The situation urgently requires the ranks of the students to strengthen their unity and solidarity and popularize their movement, it noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The pro-democracy movement in South Korea so far shows that unity is more powerful than bayonets, it said, calling upon one million students to unite themselves under the banner of Hanchongryon, the umbrella organization, irrespective of movement-influenced students or non-activist students. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Hanchongryon should be developed into a mass organization taking its roots deeper among students, it stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The appeal said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   One million students should vigorously rise in the anti-candidate campaign related to the April 13 "general election" and try all of the right-wing conservative and corrupt politicians. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They should also develop the struggle against increase of the registration fee into a struggle against the anti-social "government". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Calling for leading the spring struggle to a nationwide anti-U.S. struggle, it said the students should strongly wage a joint action and solidarity struggle with workers and people from other social strata. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   On the same day, the department made public slogans of immediate struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The slogans said that one million students should turn out in the spring struggle, get the U.S. troops, sources of murders, withdrawn from South Korea and liquidate the outdated politics through a campaign for defeating right-wing conservative and corrupt politicians.

Committee for preserving Kim Il Sung street formed in Cambodia 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 13 (KCNA) -- A committee for managing and keeping order on Generalissimo Kim Il Sung Street was formed in Phnom Penh on March 27 on the occasion of Sun's Day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The deputy mayor of Phnom Penh was appointed as its chairman. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The committee is obliged to routinely preserve and manage the street and keep order on the street.

Congratulatory letter to Kim Jong Il 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, April 13 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il received a congratulatory letter from the Economic and commercial councilors' corps here on the occasion of Sun's Day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The letter was handed to an official concerned by head of the corps Sergei Leushikin, commercial councilor of the Russian embassy, today.

Yang Hyong Sop meets foreign guests 
  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 13 (KCNA) -- Yang Hyong Sop, vice- president of the presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly and chairman of the Korean Social Scientists Society, met and conversed with foreign guests at the Mansudae Assembly Hall today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Among them were representatives of the Asian region--Garib Newaz, director of the board of the International Institute of the Juche Idea and executive director of the Asian Regional Institute of the Juche Idea, and Manik Lal Shrestha, deputy director of the AEIJI--Reggie Ranatunge, vice-Minister of Ports Development, rehabilitation and reconstruction of Sri Lanka and advisor to the Sri Lankan Society for the Study of Self-reliance, Debabrata Biswas, Indian parliamentarian, and Mustafa Jaber, chairman of the Jordanian National Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea, which came here to attend the 15th meeting of the board of the IIJI. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   At the meeting they said that President Kim Il Sung was not only the leader of the Korean people but also the great leader of all the people who aspire after independence and the Juche idea fathered by him serves as a banner of victory for the people struggling for freedom and independence, progress and prosperity.
